cat << EOF
Gdkxft transparently adds anti-aliased font support to gtk+-1.2. Once
you have installed it, you can run any (well, nearly any) existing gtk+
binary and see anti-aliased fonts in the gtk widgets. You don't need to
recompile gtk+ or your applications.
EOF
